/* 
This amalgation uses the shadertoy-iChannel-pattern:
a-abcd,b-abcd,c-abcd,d-abcd,i-abcd
Unless a an unnecessary pointer is changed to something more important
- like KeyboarIn, CubeMapA, a staric distanceField to Glyphs, or a blueNoise Texture.
the ichannels of all frasmeBuffers are identical:
iChannel0<-BuffA
iChannel1<-BuffB
iChannel2<-BuffC
iChannel3<-BuffD
To have [plugin]s that are rarely more than 1 iChannel FrameBuffer
[plugin] names are like iChannels, because thats what they point to.
This stucture lets me define global modifiable buffer pointers 
for a plugin-HotSwap option
with #ifdef iDiegeticUI contexts for missing-plugin cases:
Each [plugin] is one seperate FrameBufferObject, summarizing what they buffer:
iDiegeticUI, a lot of object parameters, to be drag and droppable, currently just 2d points.
iAD        , no DoubleBuffer, functions cannot read buffers from commonTab (shadertoy is a bit suilly here)
iCanBez    , no DoubleBuffer, this is the final composite out.
*/
