//floor(a) is a basis-function for mod() and fract() (all complement each other)
//calculus on floor() is simpler than on fract() or mod() , so we defien fract() as 1.-floor(), and not as mod(a,1.)
//and becase floor(a)=a-fract(a) is needed for differentials!
//using floor(a) as basis,simplifies automaticDiffernetiation (and it fixes mod())
v0 fl(v0 a){return floor(a);}
i0 fl(i0 a){return a;} //tautological definition of floor(int(a)) simplifies things
//multiplying by 0 seems silly, but:
//it maintains structure to multiply by *a.b *a.c *a.d
//it eases into the logic of Automatic Differentiation
d0   fl(d0   a){return d0(floor(a.a),0.*a.b);}
d00  fl(d00  a){return d00 (floor(a.a),0.*a.b,0.*a.c);}
